UNIDENTIFIED DISEASE - NEPAL
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
[1]
Date: Mon, 8 Mar 1999 11:12:52 -0600
From: C. L. Staten <sysop@emergency.com>

Viral Disease Kills 72 in Nepal, 7 Mar 1999
A so-far unidentified viral disease has killed at least 72 people, mostly
young children, in a remote mountainous village in Nepal in just two days,
a health official said on Sunday.
The village of Mahabaipatankhola, where the deaths occurred, is located in
a western mountainous area 250 miles west of the capital Katmandu and
accessible only by foot, said Mahendra Bista, chief of Nepal's Epidemiology
and Disease Control Dept. There is only one small clinic with one doctor.
Bista said the government was putting together a team of medical experts to
trek to the area. He said the virus had not been identified, but the cause
of the disease could be polluted water and/or contaminated food.
Few other details were immediately available.
