[2]
Date: Mon, 08 Mar 1999 13:25:29 -0500
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Katmandu Post, 8 Mar 1999

An outbreak of viral influenza has claimed 90 lives and affected 3,170
others in different parts of the country in the past month, the Kathmandu
Post said Monday, quoting health ministry officials. The daily said 72
persons have died in Jumla district, mid-western Nepal, 14 in neighboring
Dolpa district and 4 in Gorkha district of western Nepal.
The symptoms included fever, cough, vomiting, headache, body ache and
cramps, and most of the victims were children aged between 5 and 15, the
newspaper said. The government was preparing to send a team of experts to
the affected areas soon, it added.
